b|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/90s/1997/MM-1997-06-14.pdf|title=Music & Media: Eurochart Hot 100|accessdate=2018-01-16|work=Music & Media}}</ref> \n|align=\"center\"|62\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|55|artist=Strike|song=I Have Peace|songid=3512|accessdate=3 April 2020}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Scotland ([[Official Charts Company]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/scottish-singles-chart/19970525/41/|title=Official Scottish Singles Sales Chart Top 100 25 May 1997 \u2013 31 May 1997|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|26\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|34|artist=Strike|song=I Have Peace|accessdate=13 January 2020}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[UK Singles Chart|UK Singles]] ([[Official Charts Company]])\n|align=\"center\"|17\n|-\n{{singlechart|UKdance|11|date=19970525|accessdate=14 January 2020}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1997 singles]]\n[[Category:1997 songs]]\n[[Category:Strike (band) songs]]\n[[Category:Electro songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = I Have Peace\n| cover      = Strike-I_Have_Peace.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Strike (band)|Strike]]\n| album      = I Saw the Future\n| B-side     = Remix\n| released   = 1997\n| format     =\n*[[12\" single]]\n*[[CD single]]\n*[[CD maxi]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n*[[Electronic dance music|Dance]]\n*[[breakbeat]]\n*[[Hip hop music|hip hop]]\n| length     = 3:55\n| label      = [[Fresh Records (UK)|Fresh Records]]\n| writer     = \n*Andy Gardner \n*Karl Gordon\n*Mark King\n*Matt Cantor\n*Phil Gould\n*Wally Badarou\n| producer   = [[Strike (band)|Strike]]\n| prev_title = [[My Love Is for Real#Strike version|My Love is for Real]]\n| prev_year  = 1996\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|Czr6u38gKAU|\"I Have Peace\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''I Have Peace'''\" is a 1997 song by British [[electronic dance music]] [[musical ensemble|band]] [[Strike (band)|Strike]]. It was their fifth and last single from their only studio album, ''I Saw the Future'' and reached number 17 in the UK charts. The song also peaked at number 26 in Scotland, number 34 in Switzerland and number 55 in Germany. The chorus is sung by vocalist Victoria Newton and the rap is by K. The song received positive reviews from music critics. ''[[Music & Media]]'' wrote about the song: \"...Strike unveil a new single and new sound this week with I Have Peace, on U.K. label Fresh. This instanty appealing song is a male-voiced rap track, featuring light piano and a female sung chorus. A highly melodic and gospel influenced singalong number...\"<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/90s/1997/MM-1997-03-01.pdf|title=Dance Grooves|work=[[Music & Media]]|page=12|accessdate=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = 12\" single, United Kingdom (1997)\n\n| title1          = I Have Peace\n| note1           = Original Mix\n| length1         = \n\t\n| title2          = I Have Peace\n| note2           = Uno Clio Vocal Mix\n| length2         = \n\n| title3          = I Have Peace\n| note3           = Forthright Club Mix\n| length3         = \n\n| title4          = I Have Peace\n| note4           = Strike's Late Late Mix\n| length4         = \n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = CD single, United Kingdom (1997)\n\n| title1          = I Have Peace\n| note1           = Original Mix\n| length1         = 3:55\n\n| title2          = I Have Peace\n| note2           = Forthright 7\" Edit\n| length2         = 3:55\n\n| title3          = I Have Peace\n| note3           = Uno Clio 12\" Mix\n| length3         = 8:26\n\n| title4          = I Have Peace\n| note4           = L.F.A. Mix\n| length4         = 3:56\n\n| title5          = I Have Peace\n| note5           = K-Gee Mix\n| length5         = 3:47\n\n| title6          = I Have Peace\n| note6